The paper deals with efficient estimation of information-theoretic distances and entropy, which are commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sublinear resources (time and space) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of clustering and classification suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of data mining (cs.DM).
